Mizuryu Kei has certainly acted very unprofessionally and his behavior is worth criticizing (as far as I know, he admits as much himself), but acting like he's completely in the wrong is... utterly stupid. His grievances is not with Hololive, who have nothing to do with the whole matter, but Cover Corp. Just a reminder, Cover Corp is that godawful company that "manages" Hololive, which, among other things, involves completely failing to protect their talents from harassment, time and time again. With that in mind, it's very likely that his grievances (if not his behavior) is very much legitimate.

So the simple version of what happened is that Mizuryu Kei was working on the manga for the Hololive ALTERNATIVE project. A day or two after it was revealed, he had a Twitter meltdown declaring that he would remove all Holo-related works from his pixiv and fanbox accounts, and that he was wiping his hands completely of Hololive. These tweets were later deleted, first only the extreme tweets like (“Cover is an extremely unprofessional company” or something along those lines, as well as a few more like it), then everything from that day/night, before he locked his account completely.

Some shit was pieced together, residual Chinese Holo antis from the Taiwan event propped him up as a martyr until they discovered he was a Nanking denier, at which point they attacked him as well. He then privated his Twitter account.

The speculation is that he didn’t know that Hololive was stupidly popular overseas, and when he found out he tried to renegotiate, failed, and threw his tamper tantrum.
